      "writtenOn": "2026-04-22T15:36:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thank you for the feedback. Updated the design to address this: a new \"Host dependency\" section under Device Type: Drive describes two layers. Systemd target wiring for execution ordering (obmc-host-stop triggers obmc-drive-poweroff), and semantic validation using the existing `Inventory.Decorator.ManagedHost` interface. When the associated host is off, On/Reboot/Powercycle transitions are rejected with a D-Bus error.",
